  <paragraph identifier="/us/dod/dodi/1327.06/purpose" status="VERIFIED" level="section">
    <heading>Purpose</heading>
    <content>
      <p>In accordance with the authority in DoD Directive 5124.02, this issuance establishes policy, assigns responsibilities, and prescribes procedures for military leave, liberty, and administrative absences that:</p>
      <p>Provide uniformity amongst the Military Services in accordance with Section 704 of Title 10, United States Code (U.S.C.).</p>
      <p>Provide respite from the work environment in ways that improve performance and increase motivation.</p>
      <p>Provide time off to address personal business and personal or family emergencies that cannot be addressed through liberty.</p>
      <p>Ensure maximum use of accrued leave, minimize the loss of leave, and reduce the cost payments for unused accrued leave.</p>
    </content>
  </paragraph>

